lua-rs-port
===========

This project is an AI-assisted port (a derivative work — a translation from
C to Rust) of the PUC-Rio reference implementation of Lua 5.4.7, pinned at
upstream version 5.4.7 (see harness/source.toml). It is not a clean-room
re-implementation: the port is produced by translating the upstream C source
with structural fidelity, so it is a derivative of that source and is governed
by the upstream license below.

Lua and this port are both distributed under the MIT License. The port's own
copyright and license appear in LICENSE; the upstream copyright notice, which
the MIT License requires be retained in all copies, is reproduced verbatim
here.

The pinned, unmodified upstream source is preserved under reference/lua-5.4.7/.


